'''I.CX''' is a [[Messaging system|messaging]] and [[file sharing]] [[web application]] providing [[end-to-end encryption]] without any download or installation. It was developed by the Toronto firm EveryBit, and relies on the [[open-source license|open-source]] ''[[EveryBit.js]]'' framework.<ref>{{cite web|title=Secure messaging and username management|url=https://github.com/EveryBit-com/everybit.js|publisher=[[GitHub]]|accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref> All encryption is done [[client-side]] in the users web browser. All files and messages stored and sent using I.CX are protected with [[Advanced Encryption Standard|256-bit AES encryption]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Encrypted Communications: Tools That Keep You Safe in Cyber Space|url=http://www.techvibes.com/blog/tools-that-keep-you-safe-2014-12-23|publisher=Tech Vibes|accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref>

