'''Nicholas D. Smith''' (born 1949) is an American philosopher and James F. Miller Professor of Humanities and Professor of Philosophy at [[Lewis & Clark College]]. He won the “Outstanding Academic Book for 1994” award for his book ''Plato’s Socrates'' (with T. C. Brickhouse). Smith is known for his research on [[Ancient Greek philosophy]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nicholas Smith |url=https://college.lclark.edu/live/profiles/77-nicholas-smith |website=Lewis & Clark College |accessdate=14 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
